Text: What we achieved.
We approached this week to achieve two main goals.
One was the focus group and the second was getting started on creating the final feedback screen for our user.
We achieved the first goal and managed to get through the most of the work that we set out to accomplish for our second objective.
On Monday, we got around 400 csv files of data and started working with it in RStudio.
We also learnt how to integrate GitHub with Rstudio and as well as using Shiny for a our "final screen".
I personally worked on making some basic functions to count errors in the data set and overlaying longitude and latitude coordinates on a map using R. .
The good.We did a good job of meeting as a team and working on different aspects of the project.
Susu kindly invited us to her home on Tuesday and made us coffee to get supercharged for work.

Susu has been working on low fidelity prototypes for our visualisation and learning R.  Kiki ran the focus group and Tzu-Rara has been looking into the shiny app and did most of the talking for the weekly catch up on Friday to practice her public speaking skills.
This has been great as everyone has stepped into roles based on their preferences and learning goals.
This means that everyone has been contributing to the project and no one is being lazy!.
We've also had good conversations with classmates and lecturers to get help.
On Wednesday, we had a meeting with TonyÂ Savarimuthu to get some ideas on R and visualisations.
Then on Friday, Roro gave us a run down on what he learnt about Shiny the previous week and we helped him out by being participants in an informal focus group.
These meetings highlight the fact that working with people outside our project will be great in teaching us new ideas and speeding up the learning process for new tools.
Things to improve on as a team.
We could improve on having more structure when we meet as a team.
This would make sure that we could be a little more productive when we see each other.
I do understand that some people prefer to work this way, where they need to talk about ideas to figure what they are doing.
However, ifÂ  we spend too much time discussing and not working on concrete tasks in our project, we won't get everything done by our due dates.
The focus group went well but we had a few technical issues that delayed the start of the session, so we will need to iron that out to ensure the meetings are not elongated.
Things I could do betterDuring the week I have gone ahead and done tasks as I felt the need to make progress in our goals.
This contributes to the project, but I feel a negative consequence of this is my team mates will not get a chance to pick up the skills they were hoping to build in the project.
I seem to be always fighting an urge to get a whole bunch of work done.
I'm not really sure how everyone else views this in the team, but I will need to do a better job of communicating what I'm working on and working collaboratively on tasks.
What would I do differently?.
Use Trello to highlight what tasks need to be done and when.
For the focus group, we should show up 15-20 minute early or meet earlier in the day to test all the functions we would like to use (recording, adding participants, asking questions).
Since we have a second focus group, I'll make sure we are a better prepared for the session.
Goals for next week.
My goals for the week will be to contribute to each aspect of the project that needs to be done.
Implement Trello to keep track of all the tasks and do a better job of communicating the work I've worked on.
General thoughts and goals for next week.
There is a strange dichotomy for how I view this past week.
With hindsight, it looks like we have done a lot of work, but in the present it feels like we haven't done much at all.
There is always a thought bouncing around my brain that we are running out of time.
I also worked too much on a couple of days, where I would spend hours working on the project, followed by a few hours of emails.
I am happy to do what I can to help the team but I should also make sure to eat food!.
This upcoming week is going to be busy.
We will have to complete almost every part of the project by Thursday morning to show the second focus group the shiny app we have made.
I hope we can do it!.Peace!
Overall
